<h2 align="center">How To Prevent Fire In Your Houses!</h2>
  <p align="center">Here are 4 ways to prevent fire in your respective homes:</p><br><hr>

<div class="container" >         
  <table class="table table-bordered table-danger">
    <thead>
      <tr align="center">
        <th>Image:</th>
        <th>What To Do:</th>
        <th>Additional Information:</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td><img src="https://i.ytimg.com/vi/BbkCqq51rys/hqdefault.jpg" width="100%"></td>
        <td id="hl">Never Leave the Stove Open Without Supervision</td>
        <td id="pr">When involving the stove, the fire might spread without you knowing. So it is important to always check if the stove is on. Put away any flammable material and don't put it near the stove for it to not catch fire.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><img src="https://tse2.mm.bing.net/th?id=OIP.UVjnk4fVlbMHXH-7Ll9FIQHaF6&pid=Api&P=0" width="100%"></td>
        <td id="hl">Unplug Chargers From Sockets If Not In Use.</td>
        <td id="pr">Sockets is the source of electricity in the house. Charging a phone, table or laptop for too long can cause a fire or an explosion. The explosion could lead to a small fire then it could lead to a bigger one. make sure to unplug all chargers from the sockets or unplug your device when you think that it is over-charged. This is also to save electricity. </td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><img src="https://tse1.mm.bing.net/th?id=OIP.nkSe5GgpznxnQgnhQo--6AHaE7&pid=Api&P=0" width="100%"></td>
        <td id="hl">Flammable Items Should be in A Place Where Children Can't Access</td>
        <td id="pr">Placing flammable items within a kid's reach can cause an incident. A child can make mistakes like breaking a glass or destroying something. It won't be surprising for them to start a small fire. Especially with flammable substances. Make sure to place it in a high shelf where they can't reach.</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td><img src="http://3.bp.blogspot.com/-lMIcx91c0h8/VkjQFDauQHI/AAAAAAAAEYQ/YWiI3a4TWts/s1600/no%2Bsmokking.jpg" width="100%"></td>
        <td id="hl">Avoid Smoking</td>
        <td id="pr">If you smoke, you need to light the other end of the cigarette. Smoking inside the house can lead to a fire, especially when you didn't put out the fire when you're done smoking. Always be careful where you throw the cigarette to prevent starting a fire. Avoid smoking at all because it doesn't just start a fire, It also dangerous for the kids in the house.</td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div><hr><br>


<h3>If A Fire Does Occur, What To Do?</h3><br>

    <h6>-Prepare an emergency exit guide, beforehand.-</h6>
    <h6>-Prepare an emergency bag and kit.-</h6>
    <h6>-have copies of your important documents.-</h6>
    <h6>-Backup plan when your fire occurs in your house.-</h6>
    <h6>-Make sure that the people in the house knows what to do when a fire starts.-</h6><br>

